Brief installation instructions for TORNADO

ER Wed Jan  7 11:25:08 EST 2009
------------------------------------------

Source distribution (tornado.tar.gz):

    setenv TORNADO  (HOME) assign a location for the libraries.

    tar zxf tornado.tar.gz       Unpacks the archive. (makes a new directory, tornado). 

souce code:
----------
easel             - Sequence analysis library (SRE unpublished). svn revision 293.
tornado           - Probabilistic RNA folding with a generalized SCFG grammar

tornado executables:
------------
grm-emit      - emits sequences with secondary structures given a probabilistic RNA grammar
grm-fold      - folds an RNA sequence 
grm-score     - calculates score of an RNA structure 
grm-sseval    - simple statistics for a given RNA structure
grm-train     - trains the parameters of an RNA grammar given a training set
grm-parse     - display of an SCFG grammar


To create the executables:
-------------------------

easel
-----
cd easel
autoconf
./configure
make
(need the easel library to compile tornado)

tornado
-------
cd src
autoconf
./configure
make
